.\" termin.al-name: cv
.\" termin.al-usage: cv
.\" termin.al-summary: Open cv content.
.TH CV 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
cv \- Open cv content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
cv
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Requests the fixed virtual target
.BR ~/cv.md .
In the current browser-demo corpus that entry is deliberately locked, so no viewer is opened.
.SH FAILURES
With no arguments, cv returns the stable diagnostic
.BR "Access is locked: ~/cv.md" .
Extra arguments are rejected before target resolution. Cancellation opens nothing.
.SH NOTES
The command does not authenticate, unlock, download or expose CV content. The virtual corpus remains read-only.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ cv
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
about(1), login(1), open(1)
